Employmentstatus

Employed borrowers have less number of delinquency compared to other category of borrowers.

Borrowers APR vs Borrower Rate based on Term

Let us find if term of loan impact the interest rate and Annual Percentage Rate

As term increases,borrower APR increases with borrower interest rate forming a linear relationship.Let us look at the correlation coefficient.

## 
##  Pearson's product-moment correlation
## 
## data:  BorrowerAPR and BorrowerRate
## t = 2347.7, df = 113910, p-value < 2.2e-16
## alternative hypothesis: true correlation is not equal to 0
## 95 percent confidence interval:
##  0.9897057 0.9899409
## sample estimates:
##      cor 
## 0.989824

This shows that both the variables have strong linear relationship.

Reflection

Prosper Loan dataset is a huge dataset of more tha 1 lakh data.As I explored the data,I found success in finding pattern of loan amount based on employment status and home ownership.I found difficult to choose the variables to explore as there are 81 of them containing varied and vast information.I have analysed around 20 variables.There is a lot of scope in taking this project forward. All the variables can be analysed and plotted to check for the trend and model can be built.
